// @check
// Soundness corpus index (ROADMAP A12).
//
// This directory pins down VL's type-safety contract: every well-typed program
// is type-safe at runtime (see docs/soundness.md). Each file is a small, focused
// "must-error" or "must-not-error" program so a future deep change to inference,
// narrowing, or codegen cannot silently regress soundness — a regression flips a
// must-not-error case into an error (or vice versa) and breaks `deno task test`.
//
// The runner is STRICT BY DEFAULT (see tests/cases_test.ts): a test fails on any error
// or warning it did not declare. So the two halves of the contract are:
//   // @check / @run with NO @error  — the "must-not-error" half: the file is
//             asserting it compiles with zero diagnostics (@check = not run,
//             @run = also runs and checks `@log` output end to end). No @ok
//             directive is needed — clean compile is the default.
//   // @error / @error-at            — the "must-error" half: an unsound use is
//             rejected with a diagnostic containing the given text.
//
// KNOWN-UNSOUND corners are filed as `xfail-*.vl` with a `TODO(soundness):` note
// and currently compile clean (no @error): they encode a gap that is documented
// but not yet enforced (e.g. the permissive arithmetic hole-operand rule,
// ROADMAP A13). When the gap is closed, the xfail flips to an @error case.
//
// This file is itself a trivial must-not-error case so the directory is never
// empty.
let _corpus = 0
